data.chText: 信念；原则；纲领；宗教信仰
data.enText: a set of principles or religious beliefs

data.chText: 各种种族、肤色和宗教信仰的人
data.enText: people of all races, colours and creeds
a statement of Christian belief that is spoken as part of some church services

tr: any system of principles or beliefs
the written body of teachings of a religious group that are generally accepted by that group

value.def: A creed is a set of beliefs, principles, or opinions that strongly influence the way people live or work.

example.ex: ...their devotion to their creed of self-help.
example.tran: 他们坚信自力更生的原则

example.ex: The centre is open to all, no matter what race or creed.
example.tran: 该中心向所有人开放，不论种族和宗教信仰如何。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to believe, to trust 相信, 信任
rootsaffixes.title: creed, cred

partsOfSpeech.dec: ac 加强 + credit 信任；学分 → 信任；委任
cred 相信，信任 + ence 表行为 → 相信；凭证
cred 相信，信任 + ent 表名词 + ial …的 → 让人相信的东西 → 凭据
cred 相信，信任 + ible 可…的 → 可靠的，可信的
cred 相信，信任 + it → 信任；学分
cred 相信，信任 + ulous 多…的 → 过分相信 → 轻信的
dis 不 + credit 信任；学分 → 不信任，怀疑
in 不 + cred 相信，信任 + ulity → 不轻信
in 不 + credulous 轻信的 → 不轻信的
